Nematocysts (
Fig. 13
): A-type b-mastigophores (7.3–7.8 μm long x 1.8–2.2 μm wide); B-type b-mastigophores (15.5–18 μm long x 3.2–4.5 μm wide). Identifications of nematocyst categories are tentative; few discharged threads were observed in formalin-preserved material and their morphology was indistinct.
